org.linqs.psl.reasoner.term.streaming

Class StreamingCacheIterator<T extends ReasonerTerm>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.linqs.psl.reasoner.term.streaming.StreamingCacheIterator<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterator<T>, StreamingIterator<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DCDStreamingCacheIterator, SGDStreamingCacheIterator

    public abstract class StreamingCacheIterator<T extends ReasonerTerm>
extends Object
implements StreamingIterator<T>
    Iterate over all the terms from the disk cache. On these non-initial iterations, we will fill the term cache from disk and drain it. This iterator can be constructed as read-only. In this case, pages will not be witten to disk.

      • readPage

        protected abstract void readPage(String termPagePath,
                                 String volatilePagePath)
        Read a page and fill the termCache using freed terms from the termPool. The child is responsible for all IO, but shuffling will be handled by the parent.

      • writeVolatilePage

        protected abstract void writeVolatilePage(String volatilePagePath)
        Write a cache page to disk. Unlike readPage, the child is responsible for undoing any shuffling via shuffleMap.
